com.apriori.util

Class Stopwatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.util.Stopwatch

  • public class Stopwatch
extends Object
    A utility for measuring elapsed time. It can be stopped and restarted and the resulting elapsed time will represent time elapsed during periods when the stopwatch was "running". It also has a "lap" function so that data can be collected and retained for multiple iterations or laps.

    This class is threadsafe, so a single instance could be shared by multiple threads if need be.

    • Method Detail

      • start

        public Stopwatch start()
        Starts the stopwatch. Once started, it is "running". Time that elapses while the clock is running can be queried via read().

        If the stopwatch is already running, this method does nothing.

        Returns:
        this, for method chaining

      • stop

        public Stopwatch stop()
        Stops the stopwatch. Once stopped, it is no longer "running". Time that elapses while the watch is stopped will not be measured and will not impact queries.
        Returns:
        this, for method chaining
        See Also:
        reset()

      • lap

        public Stopwatch lap()
        Records the stopwatch's elapsed time as a lap measurement and resets the elapsed time. If the stopwatch is stopped when this method is called, it will still be stopped when this method returns.
        Returns:
        this, for method chaining

      • read

        public long read()
        Queries for the elapsed time measured by the stopwatch, in nanoseconds. This returns the total elapsed time during which the stopwatch was "running" since the last call to either lap() or reset().
        Returns:
        the elapsed time, in nanoseconds

      • read

        public long read(TimeUnit unit)
        Queries for the elapased time measured by the stopwatch, in the specified unit.
        Parameters:
        unit - the unit in which measured elapsed time is returned
        Returns:
        the elapsed time, in the specified unit
        See Also:
        read()

      • lapResults

        public long[] lapResults()
        Queries for recorded lap times, in nanoseconds. The returned array will have one value for each call to lap(). If lap() hasn't been called then the array will be empty.
        Returns:
        an array of lap times, in nanoseconds

        public double lapAverage()
